    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes COMMIT as a gap-filling approach that considers community composition and metabolite leakage, not as a consensus reconstruction generator. Consensus reconstructions are generated separately from four draft reconstruction methods (KBase, CarveMe, RAVEN 2.0, AuReMe/Pathway Tools) and then merged. COMMIT is applied to the consensus reconstructions for gap-filling, not for generating consensus. The research question conflates two distinct steps in the pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does COMMIT generate a single consensus metabolic reconstruction from multiple draft reconstructions of organisms in a microbial community?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:37.553737+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "COMMIT is explicitly named and described as the primary methodological contribution of the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "COMMIT",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:37.553737+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We then devise an approach for gap filling, termed COMMIT, that considers metabolites for secretion based on their permeability and the composition of the community. By applying COMMIT with two soil communities from the Arabidopsis thaliana culture collection, we could significantly reduce the gap-filling solution in comparison to filling gaps in individual reconstructions without affecting the genomic support.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper produces gap-filled consensus metabolic reconstructions, but the consensus generation is a separate step from COMMIT. COMMIT's output is gap-filled reconstructions (functional models), not the consensus reconstructions themselves. The consensus reconstructions are generated first by merging draft reconstructions from four methods, then COMMIT gap-fills them.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Consensus metabolic reconstruction for each organism",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:37.553737+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We then apply COMMIT to high-quality consensus metabolic reconstructions based on genomes of the isolates from the Arabidopsis thaliana microbial culture collections, At-SPHERE, for two different soil community compositions [36,37].",
      "asbval:note": "The paper applies COMMIT to Arabidopsis thaliana-associated soil communities, but COMMIT is not a 'consensus reconstruction pipeline'\u2014it is a gap-filling pipeline that operates on pre-generated consensus reconstructions. The consensus reconstructions are generated from four separate draft reconstruction methods (KBase, CarveMe, RAVEN 2.0, AuReMe/Pathway Tools) before COMMIT is applied.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title_scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the COMMIT consensus metabolic reconstruction pipeline for Arabidopsis thaliana communities",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:37.553737+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card conflates two distinct methodological steps: (1) consensus reconstruction generation (merging draft reconstructions from four methods) and (2) gap-filling with community-aware constraints (COMMIT). COMMIT is the gap-filling step, not the consensus generation step.",
        "The card's research question asks how COMMIT generates consensus reconstructions, but the paper shows that consensus reconstructions are generated separately by merging outputs from KBase, CarveMe, RAVEN 2.0, and AuReMe/Pathway Tools. COMMIT then gap-fills these pre-existing consensus reconstructions.",
        "The title 'COMMIT consensus metabolic reconstruction pipeline' is misleading. COMMIT is a gap-filling approach, not a consensus reconstruction approach. The consensus reconstruction is generated upstream of COMMIT."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:37.553737+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "The research question accurately captures the core mechanism of COMMIT as described in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does COMMIT's community-dependent gap-filling procedure use metabolic context from multiple community members to fill gaps in individual consensus reconstructions?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
