    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We applied COMMIT to two soil microbial communities whose composition was determined by comparison of 16S rRNA sequences from environmental samples with those from the cross-reference operational taxonomic units (OTU) used in At-SPHERE [38]. This resulted in 20 and 24 recovered soil isolates from two respective studies, referred to as 'Bulgarelli' [37] and 'Schlaeppi' [36]. The draft metabolic reconstructions for the members of the two communities were gap-filled by applying COMMIT with 100 iterations, corresponding to different random orderings, and an initial gap-filling medium containing only D-glucose as a carbon source.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates application of COMMIT to produce gap-filled models for community members. The annotation of filled reactions is implicit in the gap-filling procedure and explicitly discussed in the methods section regarding sequence support for added reactions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Gap-filled metabolic models for each community member with filled reactions annotated",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:52.710968+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_363932874__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses on the gap-filling step for Arabidopsis thaliana microbial communities, which is directly addressed in the paper. The paper applies COMMIT to two specific soil communities (Schlaeppi and Bulgarelli) derived from At-SPHERE, which are Arabidopsis thaliana-associated microbial communities.",
        "The card does not mention consensus reconstruction generation, which is a prerequisite step in the paper's workflow. However, the card's focus on the gap-filling step itself is appropriate and well-supported."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:51:52.710968+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "The research question accurately captures the core purpose of COMMIT as described in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Infer and fill metabolic gaps in individual organism models by leveraging shared metabolic context and dependencies across community members. This skill applies constraint-based reasoning to propose reactions that bridge gaps in consensus reconstructions using multi-organism meta",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We then apply COMMIT to high-quality consensus metabolic reconstructions based on genomes of the isolates from the Arabidopsis thaliana microbial culture collections, At-SPHERE, for two different soil community compositions",
      "asbval:note": "The paper applies COMMIT to plant-associated microbial communities (Arabidopsis thaliana), matching the scope description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have consensus metabolic reconstructions for multiple community members (e.g., plant-associated microbes or plant-microbial consortia) and those individual models contain incomplete or disconnected metabolic pathways.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Since members of microbial communities are often dependent on each other, gap-filling solutions of the community members must also be put into context of the community in which the organisms co-exist. In addition, the usage of gap-filled solutions and exudates from other community members may further reduce the overall number of added reactions to fill in the gaps in the metabolic reconstruction for the community.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly states that community context is essential for gap-filling and that metabolite exchange between members reduces gaps.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when metabolic gaps cannot be filled from single-organism databases alone, but the community context reveals shared substrates, products, or exchange requirements that suggest plausible gap-filling reactions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To address this issue, several algorithms for gap filling, applicable to single and community reconstructions [13], have been proposed; however, they are not feasible to gap fill reconstructions of large communities (as described e.g. in [27,28]) due to the sheer amount of computational resources required.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper implies COMMIT is designed for draft reconstructions with gaps, not fully curated models.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input reconstructions already fully gap-filled or curated from complete enzymatic databases",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The existing gap-filling medium as well as the order in which gap-filling is applied plays a very important role in the reconstructed model [29]. The problem of finding metabolic interactions within microbial communities using constraint-based methods has been addressed by multiple studies, focussing on pairwise or higher-level interactions [8,10,30\u201334].",
      "asbval:note": "The paper emphasizes that COMMIT is designed for community context, implying single-organism gap-filling is a different approach.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Single-organism models with no community context available; use organism-specific gap-filling instead",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "COMMIT is the primary tool described in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "COMMIT",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-dependent-reaction-inference/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "COMMIT starts with a minimal medium; secreted metabolites from gap-filled (i.e. functional) models are then determined and used to enlarge the medium, thereby shaping the overall gap-filling solution over the course of each random ordering.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes COMMIT's operation on consensus reconstructions with metabolite exchange to fill gaps.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-dependent-reaction-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[0].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Implements community-dependent gap-filling module that operates on consensus reconstructions and uses metabolic overlap to infer missing reactions across community members",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:29.018118+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
