    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We then devise an approach for gap filling, termed COMMIT, that considers metabolites for secretion based on their permeability and the composition of the community... the consensus of automatically generated metabolic reconstructions improves the quality of the draft reconstructions",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does generate consensus reconstructions from multiple draft reconstructions, but the consensus approach does NOT retain 'only reactions and metabolites conserved across all input models.' Instead, passage [5] states: 'The consensus generation consisted of matching metabolite, reaction, and gene identifiers... We employed cosine similarity to identify reactions of similar stoichiometry that may have opposite directions, lack protons or whose coefficients differ by a factor.' The consensus merges complementary information from multiple approaches rather than retaining only conserved elements. The card's description is overly restrictive and mischaracterizes the actual consensus method.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Synthesize a single consensus metabolic model from multiple draft genome-scale reconstructions of organisms in a microbial community by identifying and retaining only reactions and metabolites conserved across all input models.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:42.251121+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We then devise an approach for gap filling, termed COMMIT, that considers metabolites for secretion based on their permeability and the composition of the community. By applying COMMIT with two soil communities from the Arabidopsis thaliana culture collection, we could significantly reduce the gap-filling solution in comparison to filling gaps in individual reconstructions",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates reduction in gap-filling solution size and improved quality through consensus approach.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This approach enables faithful representation of community metabolism while reducing redundancy and improving model interpretability.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:42.251121+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We used the high-quality draft genomes for 432 isolates available from At-SPHERE [38] to obtain their draft genome-scale metabolic reconstructions. To this end, we applied four widely-used, fully automated approaches for metabolic network reconstruction relying on few parameters, namely: KBase [19], CarveMe [14], RAVEN 2.0 [17], and AuReMe/ Pathway Tools [15,16]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses draft reconstructions from multiple approaches for organisms from ecological communities (Arabidopsis thaliana culture collections).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have draft metabolic reconstructions (in SBML or equivalent format) for multiple organisms sampled from a single ecological community",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:42.251121+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The consensus generation consisted of matching metabolite, reaction, and gene identifiers... We then applied COMMIT to high-quality consensus metabolic reconstructions based on genomes of the isolates from the Arabidopsis thaliana microbial culture collections, At-SPHERE, for two different soil community compositions",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly performs consensus generation first, then applies COMMIT gap-filling to the consensus reconstructions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "particularly before performing community-dependent gap-filling",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:42.251121+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "COMMIT is the primary tool described in the paper for gap-filling and community-dependent metabolic reconstruction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "COMMIT",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:42.251121+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "COMMIT relies on the FastGapFilling algorithm, which optimizes a weighted sum of the fluxes through the biomass and additional candidate reactions by using linear programming (LP) formulation",
      "asbval:note": "COMMIT performs community-dependent gap-filling (yes), but consensus generation is a separate step performed before COMMIT. Passage [5] states: 'The consensus generation consisted of matching metabolite, reaction, and gene identifiers... We then applied COMMIT to high-quality consensus metabolic reconstructions.' Consensus generation uses STATIS method and cosine similarity matching, not COMMIT. COMMIT is applied after consensus generation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "community-metabolic-reconstruction-synthesis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "COMMIT performs consensus generation and community-dependent gap-filling for metabolic model integration from multiple draft reconstructions",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T09:52:42.251121+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolic-gap-filling-community-context/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe COMMIT, a constraint-based approach that respects the composition of the microbial community and metabolite leakage in the process of gap filling metabolic reconstructions of the respective community members.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes COMMIT as a community-aware gap-filling approach that considers community composition and metabolite exchange.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009906",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolic-gap-filling-community-context",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Community-dependent gap-filling leverages shared metabolic context across multiple microbial or plant community members to identify and fill metabolic gaps in individual consensus reconstructions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
